The paper deals with consensus algorithms in distributed computing, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The use of convex polytopes and Euclidean space suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). The paper also involves optimization, which could place it in the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Information Theory (cs.IT).
